Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.22,0:01:13.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历史频道 - 宇宙 第4季第1集 死星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The History Channel - The Universe s04e01 Death Stars
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.24,0:01:18.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离地球数千光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thousands of light-years from the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.74,0:01:23.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗超大质量恒星正在启动自我毁灭的按钮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a supermassive star is preparing to hit the self-destruct button.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.75,0:01:28.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间每天都有恒星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars explode every day in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.00,0:01:31.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过这一个与众不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but this one is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:36.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它蛰伏在人马座 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It lurks in the constellation Sagittarius,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.26,0:01:39.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄道十二星座里的神话射手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mythological archer of the celestial zodiac.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:46.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此星叫做WR 104\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The star is called WR 104,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.94,0:01:50.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其破坏力可能针对我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its destructive force could be targeting us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.61,0:01:54.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正瞄准着我们这颗脆弱的蓝色星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and taking aim at our fragile blue planet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.61,0:02:00.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其致命的辐射将点燃我们的臭氧保护层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with enough deadly radiation to ignite our protective ozone layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.32,0:02:04.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这将激起剧烈的气候变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This would incite drastic climate change,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:07.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成许多动植物种的灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cause the extinction of many plant and animal species,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.83,0:02:12.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至人类的消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and potentially the demise of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:21.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,WR 104只是宇宙间数以百万计的大死亡之星中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WR 104 is just one of millions of massive death stars in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.55,0:02:26.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些凶险的天体是暮年巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These savage celestial bodies are aging giants,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.68,0:02:30.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正安排着自我爆发以进入星际来世\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}preparing to blast themselves into a stellar afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.40,0:02:34.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时 星体的表层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At that point, the outer layers of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:36.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已无任何东西留下来支撑它们抵抗重力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have nothing left to support them against gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.99,0:02:38.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样它们突然向内塌落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they suddenly fall inwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.95,0:02:48.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们最后一口气可以引发已知宇宙间最大的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their last breath can ignite the biggest explosion in the known universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:50.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线爆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:54.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发远超过我们的太阳整个100亿年生命中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a blast far exceeding the energy output of our own Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:02:57.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所输出的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over its entire 10-billion-year life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.22,0:03:04.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是其击中地球 我们所知的生命将不复存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If one were to target the Earth, life as we know it could cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:09.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是WR 104可能发生的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what could happen with WR 104,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.60,0:03:12.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正使其成为现实生活的死星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making it a real-life death star.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.27,0:03:18.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在影片《星球大战》中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the film "Star Wars,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:21.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死星是邪恶势力的终极武器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Death Star is the dark side's ultimate weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:26.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掠夺星纯属科幻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The predatory star is pure science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.54,0:03:30.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是现实中要更为恐怖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the reality is much scarier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:35.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现实生活中的死星是恒星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A death star in real life is a star that blows up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.08,0:03:39.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以致命的辐射冲击附近所有的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and blasts any nearby planets with deadly radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:42.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 那就是真正的死星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You know, that's a real death star.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.55,0:03:51.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,WR 104是所谓的沃尔夫-拉叶星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WR 104 is what's known as a Wolf-Rayet star.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:54.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是宇宙间最大的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are the largest stars in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.23,0:03:58.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比我们太阳大30倍的巨兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hulking beasts 30 times bigger than our own Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:01.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,个个都在倒数计时至世界末日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each of them counting down to Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.70,0:04:11.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,法国天文学家查尔斯 沃尔夫和乔治 拉叶在1867年发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Discovered by French astronomers Charles Wolf and Georges Rayet in 1867,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:15.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星是宇宙中的歹徒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wolf-Rayet stars are the outlaws of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.21,0:04:18.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星的生存有其信条 - \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars live by the credo,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.50,0:04:22.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命短暂者 英年早逝 留下漂亮的躯壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Live fast, die young, leave a good-looking corpse."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:26.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们越大 生命就越短\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the bigger they are, the faster they live,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.14,0:04:29.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命越短 死亡就越暴戾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the faster they live, the more violent their end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:35.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们通过极快地燃烧自己的核燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They burn through their nuclear fuel extremely quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.81,0:04:38.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耗尽自己所有的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and exhaust everything that they have,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.11,0:04:40.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它们生命不会很长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so consequently they don't live very long,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:42.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至多也就几千万年而已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe a few tens of millions of years at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:46.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们很容易找到 因为它们是星际王国中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're easy to find, because they're the real T. rexes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:47.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真正的霸王龙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the stellar kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们强大无比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're immensely powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.45,0:04:56.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2000年 澳洲天文学家彼得 塔特希尔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the year 2000, Australian astronomer Peter Tuthill
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:02.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始研究沃尔夫-拉叶星104 距离地球约8000光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}began studying Wolf-Rayet 104, some 8,000 light-years from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.17,0:05:08.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗巨星的凶险与众不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This giant was ominously different from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.43,0:05:15.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,塔特希尔的团队立马就注意到了其周围巨大的尘埃云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tuthill's team immediately noticed an immense dust cloud around it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.56,0:05:19.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比我们整个太阳系大了20倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}20 times larger than our entire solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.27,0:05:22.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道沃尔夫-拉叶星104周围存在着尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We knew there was dust around WoIf-Rayet 104,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.36,0:05:24.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让人大惑不解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that was a puzzle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:27.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那就好象是发现了地狱里的雪花一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's a bit like finding a snowflake in hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.74,0:05:30.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是个谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was a mystery there,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.87,0:05:32.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们试图解决这个谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we wanted to try and solve that mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.37,0:05:39.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的六年中 塔特希尔利用夏威夷的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the course of six years, Tuthill used an infrared camera
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.33,0:05:41.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,凯克天文台的红外摄像机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the Keck Observatory in Hawaii
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.67,0:05:45.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过多重曝光创建了一个复合图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create a composited image from multiple exposures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.76,0:05:51.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它产生了惊人的延时排列\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It yielded an amazing time-lapse sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.26,0:05:56.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,104星正在形成一个怪异的螺旋尘埃柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}104 was producing an exotic spiraling plume of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:05:59.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它让人震惊不已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was almost a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.73,0:06:00.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我第一次看到时简直不敢相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I didn't believe it when I first saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.86,0:06:03.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想 恒星看上去不会是螺旋的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I thought, stars don't look like spirals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.07,0:06:04.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我看过的书中从未有过螺旋的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no spiral I've ever seen in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:06.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们于是手忙脚乱起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We then had a mad scramble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.28,0:06:07.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须努力了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We had to try and understand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.86,0:06:10.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星怎么会产生这个漂亮的尾巴的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how a star can produce this elegant tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.95,0:06:16.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,塔特希尔发现这个怪异的尘埃螺旋的关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tuthill discovered that the key to this strange dust spiral
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.41,0:06:20.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在于事实上WR 104不是孤立的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the fact that WR 104 wasn't alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.67,0:06:23.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它与一颗较小的恒星一起被锁定在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's locked in orbit with a smaller star
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.34,0:06:25.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所谓的双星系的轨道上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in what's known as a binary system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:32.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,双星喷射出的大量的带电粒子叫做星风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Both stars eject masses of charged particles called stellar winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.55,0:06:35.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些风在宇宙中并不罕见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These winds aren't uncommon in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:40.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳产生的太阳风吹过了外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our own Sun creates a solar wind that extends beyond the outer planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.73,0:06:44.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所不同的是 双星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The difference is that, in a binary system,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.36,0:06:46.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星风来自两颗恒星的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when winds from the two stars collide,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.86,0:06:50.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气体压缩了 烟尘就产生了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gases are compressed, and dust and soot are created.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:55.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是究竟是什么引起这种尘埃形成了这样奇特的螺旋的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what causes this dust to form into such an exotic spiral?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.71,0:07:03.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草坪洒水器倒是个不错的比喻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it turns out that a lawn sprinkler makes a great analogy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.75,0:07:08.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来阐述发生在这些碰撞风的双星系里的物理学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to illustrate the physics that's occurring in these colliding-wind binary systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.76,0:07:09.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们改造了这个洒水器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've modified this sprinkler
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.97,0:07:12.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使其龙头只能射出一股水流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it only shoots one jet out of the spigot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.09,0:07:17.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单股水流代表源源不断的尘埃粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The single water jet represents the constant flow of dust particles
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:19.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由碰撞星风产生出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}being created by the colliding stellar winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.94,0:07:25.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是因为WR 104星系里的两颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But because the two stars in WR 104's system
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.11,0:07:27.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运行在相互缠绕的轨道上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are in constant orbit around each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.82,0:07:31.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对尘埃流附加了圆周运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it adds a circular motion to the stream of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:36.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的第一直觉就是水流在进行圆周运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Your first intuition is that the water is moving in a circular motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.41,0:07:38.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但事实上 草坪洒水器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in actual fact, the lawn sprinkler
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:41.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实射出的是一条直线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is really shooting a jet in a straight line.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:42.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水滴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The water droplets,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.62,0:07:45.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使它们是从洒水器里直线射出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even though they're moving in a straight line away from the spigot,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:47.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也产生了一个弧线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they create an arc,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.30,0:07:50.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弧线缠绕在了旋转的螺旋里了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that arc wrapped into a spiral with the rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.13,0:07:54.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,螺旋甚至产生了更多的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spiral spawned even more questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:56.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最头痛的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most troubling--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.30,0:08:01.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,WR 104究竟会成为何种死星呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exactly what kind of death star could WR 104 become?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:05.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星可以被视为是定时炸弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wolf-Rayet stars can be thought of as sort of a time bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.73,0:08:08.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们个头庞大 所以它们无法生存很久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they're so massive that they can't live for very long,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.03,0:08:11.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦它们燃尽它们所有的核燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and once they've burned up all of their nuclear fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:16.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就无任何东西留下以支持星体抵抗重力无情的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's nothing left to support the star against the relentless pull of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.57,0:08:19.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到那时 星核塌缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And at that point the core of the star collapses,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:23.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表层随之塌落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the outer layers fall in on top of it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.37,0:08:25.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在巨大的爆炸中向外弹出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and bounce outward in a tremendous explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.84,0:08:32.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个爆炸就是超新星 巨大的辐射爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The explosion is a supernova, an immense burst of radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:35.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短暂照亮整个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that briefly outshines an entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.43,0:08:43.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星104肯定会成为超新星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wolf-Rayet 104 will definitely go supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:47.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在未来的几十万年里的某个时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometime in the next few hundred thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.53,0:08:52.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相距8000光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At 8,000 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.90,0:08:55.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸本身不会对地球构成威胁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the explosion itself poses no threat to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.74,0:09:00.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是不排除该超新星会引发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's a chance the supernova will trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.12,0:09:02.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间最狂暴的事件 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most violent event in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:04.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:13.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些大质量死星中比例不大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a small percentage of these massive death stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.26,0:09:15.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gamma ray burst is triggered
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.30,0:09:20.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是垂死之星挤压转变成黑洞所引发的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the crushing transformation of a dying star into a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.89,0:09:25.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在恒星塌缩的过程中 它会产生一个巨大的电场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a star collapses, it produces a massive electric field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.89,0:09:29.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞬间 电场产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in an instant, the energy from this electric field
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.06,0:09:32.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转换成了物质和反物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is turned into matter and antimatter particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.61,0:09:34.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是由于相互之间的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which then collide with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.36,0:09:36.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了巨大的能量脉冲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and produce a huge pulse of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:43.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是电磁频谱中最强大的能量束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are the most powerful energy beams in the electromagnetic spectrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.12,0:09:48.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杀伤力胜过微波 红外能 甚至X射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more lethal than microwaves, infrared energy, and even X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.09,0:09:55.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类已经学会利用致命的伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans have learned to harness deadly gamma rays
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:59.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,派上有益的用途 诸如食品辐照\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for useful purposes, such as food irradiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.93,0:10:01.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过利用伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By using gamma rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.55,0:10:06.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食品加工可以消除微生物 细菌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}food processors can eliminate microorganisms, bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:09.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,病毒以及虫类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}viruses, and insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.19,0:10:11.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是伽玛射线的施加量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the amount of gamma radiation applied
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:18.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是星际伽玛射线暴所释放能量的极微小的一丁点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is an extremely tiny fraction of the energy released in a stellar gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:23.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴所产生的巨大辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gamma ray bursts produce so much radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.20,0:10:26.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于要是我们在地球上创造一个伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that if we were to create a gamma ray burst on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.79,0:10:31.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会像是无数核弹同时引爆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be like a huge number of nuclear bombs going off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:33.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会摧毁地球上的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be devastating for life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.30,0:10:39.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于人类来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the human race,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:43.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有关伽玛射线暴最关键的信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most critical piece of information about gamma ray bursts
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.10,0:10:44.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它射击的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the direction of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:47.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在塌缩的那一刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the moment of collapse,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.02,0:10:51.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星变成致密 扁平的圆盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star becomes a dense, flattened disk,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:53.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转轴的两极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the rotational axis poles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:56.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是其密集星际物质释放的唯一出路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are its only openings free of dense star matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.65,0:11:04.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会看到沿着两极的两个对应的排泄区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You get two relatively evacuated regions along the poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.28,0:11:08.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物质可以沿着那两个方向喷出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's along those directions that material can be ejected,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.95,0:11:12.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为遇到的阻力相对较小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it encounters relatively little resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:16.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个酸奶瓶提供了一个很好的比喻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this container of yogurt provides a nice analogy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.17,0:11:18.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来说明伽玛射线暴里所发生的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for what happens in a gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:21.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我将投下这只酸奶瓶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm going to drop the container of yogurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.84,0:11:25.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为瓶子有侧边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and because of the sides of the container,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:29.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,酸奶是不能够沿着这些方向出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}yogurt is not going to be able to go out along those directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.98,0:11:32.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是瓶子的顶部是敞开的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the top of the container is open,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.27,0:11:35.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此酸奶会沿着顶部喷出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so yogurt is going to squirt out along the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.27,0:11:38.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来看看发生的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Watch what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.53,0:11:43.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,酸奶基本上是直接往上喷出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the yogurt went squirting basically straight up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.53,0:11:46.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不能从旁边出来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It couldn't go out the sides, 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.15,0:11:48.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为被奶瓶的侧边给挡住了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it was blocked by the sides of the yogurt container.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.46,0:11:55.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是对伽玛射线暴里所发生情况的很好的比喻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's a nice analogy for what happens in a gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.21,0:12:00.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类最为关切的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The greatest concern for humans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:04.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴所对准的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the direction that the gamma ray burst is firing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:08.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果塌缩恒星的轴指向我们的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the axis of the collapsing star is pointing in our direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.72,0:12:11.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就会陷入严重的险境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we could be in serious trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:16.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,彼得 塔特希尔小组在研究WR104的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Peter Tuthill's team studied the plane of orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:21.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尘埃柱的轨道平面时 得到了惊人的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of WR 104's dust plume, they came to a shocking realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.99,0:12:26.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个螺旋解开这大量秘密的关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This spiral was the key that unlocked a lot of these secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.57,0:12:29.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事情开始变得有点吓人的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And where things start to get a little scary
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:32.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在于这个星系 乍看之下 几乎是正面迎对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that this system, at first blush, appears to be almost face-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:37.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们正对着轴心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're looking right down the axis at the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.42,0:12:41.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它看上去就像是一只盘子 餐盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like looking at a plate, a dinner plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.55,0:12:44.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你拿起那个平面 把它跟视线有点倾斜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you take that plane, and you tilt it to the line of sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:46.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看上去就是倾斜的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it looks inclined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:48.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就再也看不到一个圆圆的餐盘了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're no longer looking at a circular dinner plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:54.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进一步研究表明尘埃柱的旋转轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Further examination suggests the rotational axis of the dust plume
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.48,0:12:59.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎与沃尔夫-拉叶星本身的旋转轴相吻合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}appears to match the rotational axis of the Wolf-Rayet star itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.86,0:13:04.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这意味着地球直接就在枪口上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meaning the Earth is staring directly down the barrel of a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说 要是这颗恒星爆发成为伽玛射线暴时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means that if this star becomes a gamma ray burst when it blows up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:15.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两股射流之一会朝我们而来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the two jets will be pointing toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:22.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星104漂亮的螺旋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The beautiful spiral of Wolf-Rayet 104
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:26.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,突然成了厄运的使者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is suddenly a messenger of doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:34.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离地球约8000光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some 8,000 light-years from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.27,0:13:37.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗恒星被锁定在一个引力舞蹈中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}two stars are locked in a gravitational dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.23,0:13:44.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其星风在优美的螺旋中喷射出巨大的尘埃云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}their stellar winds ejecting a vast cloud of dust in a graceful spiral.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.82,0:13:48.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这对星际伙伴远不止光有一条漂亮的尾巴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's more to this star couple than just a beautiful tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:54.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两者中较大者 沃尔夫-拉叶104星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The larger of the two, Wolf-Rayet 104,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:58.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一颗大死星 濒临爆发成为一颗超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a massive death star on the verge of exploding as a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.00,0:14:01.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那基本可以肯定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That much is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.21,0:14:03.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真正的奥秘在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The real mystery is,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.84,0:14:07.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是否会释放出伽玛射线暴(GRB)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will it also unleash a gamma ray burst, or GRB,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.88,0:14:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间最强的能量爆发呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most powerful burst of energy in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:16.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题在于事关整个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The question is an important one for all on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.98,0:14:22.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其要考虑该星轴可能正指向我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}especially considering the star's axis may be pointing directly at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.86,0:14:24.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着一旦它爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means that when it blows up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:28.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它成为一个伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if it becomes a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.28,0:14:30.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射流就会直接射向我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the jet could be pointing straight at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.71,0:14:46.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,WR104在人马座里倒数计时至毁灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WR 104 is counting down to destruction in the constellation Sagittarius.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.43,0:14:53.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由罗马占星家在2000多年前命名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Named by Roman astrologers over 2,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.47,0:14:56.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人马座是拉丁语里的射手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sagittarius is Latin for The Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.73,0:15:00.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必定会问\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you have to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.85,0:15:02.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,古人或许了解了什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe were the ancients onto something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:05.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射手瞄准我们是否与什么有关？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is there something to do with The Archer aiming at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.24,0:15:13.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,WR 104可以看作是一支箭指向我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WR 104 can be thought of as an arrow pointing our way,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.41,0:15:15.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它确实爆发成为伽玛射线暴的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if indeed it blows up as a gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.08,0:15:21.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在的天文学家已几乎没有争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is little dispute among today's astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:24.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴发出的集束射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that a tightly focused beam from a gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:27.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会在太空中穿行遥远的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will travel vast distances in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.59,0:15:33.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 在2009年4月23日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, on April 23, 2009,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.26,0:15:37.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环绕地球的斯威夫特多波长观测站\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Swift multiwavelength observatory orbiting the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.14,0:15:42.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,记录到一个距离地球130亿光年的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}recorded a GRB that occurred 13 billion light-years away from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.94,0:15:45.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎就在可见宇宙的边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near the very edge of the visible universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:55.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发就发生在大爆炸后6 5亿年前后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast occurred only about 630 million years after the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:15:58.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这意味着爆发恒星所发出的伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This means that gamma rays from the exploding star
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.45,0:16:01.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以光速穿行了130亿光年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}traveled at the speed of light for 13 billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.87,0:16:04.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才让我们看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before they were visible to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:06.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使这个伽玛射线暴成为了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making this gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.59,0:16:09.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已知宇宙间最古老的星际物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the oldest stellar object in the known universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.80,0:16:13.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道没有恒星或星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know of no star or galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:16.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有比这个伽玛射线暴更加遥远的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's farther away than this gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.30,0:16:19.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是所见过的最遥远 最孤立的天体了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the single most distant, discrete object ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:24.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅8000光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At only 8,000 light-years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:29.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星104的伽玛射线暴可能是灾难性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a GRB blast from Wolf-Rayet 104 could be catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:34.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沃尔夫-拉叶星104爆发时 我们所看到的闪光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The flash that we would see if Wolf-Rayet 104 went off
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.95,0:16:36.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会比太阳亮N多倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be much brighter than the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.03,0:16:39.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是伽玛射线能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}especially at gamma ray energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:45.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单个伽玛射线暴可以轻而易举超过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A single gamma ray burst can easily exceed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:50.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数百万个星系所发出的总的光量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the total light output of millions of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.01,0:16:55.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些星系中每一个都含有上千亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And each of those galaxies contains a hundred billion stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.01,0:17:02.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种死亡之星是滴答作响的定时炸弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This death star is a ticking time bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.93,0:17:07.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家知道它无疑会成为超新星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists know for sure it will go supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:11.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是问题就在于它有可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But questions remain about its potential
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.28,0:17:15.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放的伽玛射线暴直接对准地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to unleash a gamma ray burst in the direction of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:19.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先我们需要进行确认\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the first point we need to establish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.24,0:17:20.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它会产生伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it does produce a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:23.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴是否就指向我们呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that gamma ray burst pointing towards us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.50,0:17:27.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该星的旋转轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spiraling axis of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.54,0:17:30.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎对着地球的方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}appears to be aimed in the direction of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.67,0:17:33.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是经过了数千光年的穿行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But with thousands of light-years to travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.05,0:17:36.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴的射流会真的击中目标吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would the GRB beam actually hit the target?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.59,0:17:40.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射手之箭真是那回事吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Would The Archer's aim be true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:43.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道它大致指向我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know it's pointing roughly toward us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.89,0:17:46.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它可指得够远的了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it could be pointing sufficiently away
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:49.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是伽玛射线暴发出的辐射束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the beam of radiation from the gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.65,0:17:51.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没准它变成伽玛射线暴后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if it turns into a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.40,0:17:52.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上会和我们擦肩而过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will actually miss us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.90,0:18:01.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 要是该星对准了 一个强大的能量爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, if the star is aligned, one powerful burst of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.20,0:18:09.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以将地球的臭氧层变成放射线的炼狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could turn the Earth's ozone layer into a radioactive inferno.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:16.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是数千光年外的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even a gamma ray burst that's thousands of light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.59,0:18:21.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也会将臭氧层消耗到现有水平的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could deplete the ozone layer to roughly half of its current level.
