Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.67,0:24:35.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常它会喷到百万光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Normally it would propagate up to about a million light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.80,0:24:38.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在3C321的特殊案例里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in the special case of 3C321,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.26,0:24:41.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射流猛击伙伴星系那一边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that jet is slamming into the side of a companion galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.77,0:24:43.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这情况下 它就变得撕裂了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in doing so, it's becoming disrupted
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.89,0:24:45.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扭曲了 弯曲了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and distorted and bent away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.52,0:24:49.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这给那颗伙伴星系施加了种种暴行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's wreaking all sorts of havoc to that companion galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.19,0:24:52.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像建筑物偏转了水柱一般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much like the building is deflecting the water jet,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.78,0:24:55.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,受害星系里的行星和恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planets and stars in the victimized galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.99,0:24:58.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,偏转了大部分攻击的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are deflecting most of the attacking particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.83,0:25:05.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这条射流实际上是巨大的能量粒子束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this jet is actually a massive beam of energy and particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.42,0:25:06.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些粒子处于超高温状态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these particles have been superheated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.00,0:25:09.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了等离子体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such that they form a plasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.50,0:25:13.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子体是超高温的带电粒子和离子的混合体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Plasma is a mix of super-hot charged electrons and ions
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.63,0:25:17.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞巨大的磁场将其注入射流中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}funneled into the jet by the black hole's immense magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.97,0:25:20.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此冲出黑洞的射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So jets that race out of black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.18,0:25:22.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是极具能量的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are actually incredibly energetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.14,0:25:24.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 它们可以加速粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, in fact, they can accelerate particles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.18,0:25:26.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到发出光 甚至伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such that they emit light, maybe even up to gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.60,0:25:28.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些射线强劲得惊人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These rays are incredibly powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.19,0:25:32.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且相当持久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And very long-lasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.98,0:25:36.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有估计认为死星系喷发的能量束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some estimates say the energy jet from the Death Star Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.70,0:25:39.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经持续了近200万年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been firing for nearly two million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.37,0:25:46.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了获得燃料 3C321简直生吞了整个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For its fuel, 3C321 simply devoured an entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.08,0:25:50.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它获得了大量的燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's got a lot of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.54,0:25:51.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为现在所发生的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we actually think is happening here
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.92,0:25:54.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是先前曾有过兼并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that there's been a previous merger,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.88,0:25:57.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而另一个星系已经坠入了主星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so another galaxy has fallen into the main galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.93,0:25:59.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们来看这条漂亮的尘埃带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see this beautiful dust lane,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.55,0:26:02.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味了那个星系已被撕碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which implies that the galaxy's been shredded already.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.47,0:26:06.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果撕扯行为将物质赶进了黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so that act of shredding drives mass down onto the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.89,0:26:12.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在耗尽另一个星系所提供的等离子粒子后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After consuming another galaxy's provision of plasma particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.40,0:26:16.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死星系得设法将粒子激发成射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Death Star Galaxy has to somehow energize the particles into a jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.07,0:26:20.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞具有强大的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes have powerful magnetic fields
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.78,0:26:22.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和超高速的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and superfast spin rates,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.91,0:26:26.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两者结合怎么都得引发粒子射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a combination that somehow ignites the particle jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.96,0:26:31.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为射流往一个方向发射的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe the reason the jets fire in one direction
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.75,0:26:35.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必定与所有的粒子气体围绕着黑洞运转有关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has to do with all the dust and gas circling the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.13,0:26:40.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在3C321这样的活跃星系的案例里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the case of an active galaxy like 3C321,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.76,0:26:43.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中心有一个超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has a supermassive black hole in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.26,0:26:47.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你通常会看到一个面包圈 或环状 物质团团围住它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll often have a doughnut, or torus, of material surrounding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.73,0:26:53.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此情况下 黑洞附近的高能粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In that case, highly energetic particles near the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.36,0:26:57.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是无法从通过面包圈的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can't emerge from that region through the doughnut
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.40,0:26:59.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着星系的平面喷出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along the plane of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.11,0:27:02.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只能顺着这个轴喷出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can only emerge along this axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.45,0:27:05.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里相对较少阻挡的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where there's relatively little obstructing material.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.79,0:27:10.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不行的是其伙伴星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately for the companion galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.71,0:27:13.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就眼睁睁地笔直地掉入了面包圈的洞里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's staring straight down the doughnut hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.84,0:27:15.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射流的影响区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the jet's zone of impact
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.80,0:27:19.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宛如宇宙霰弹枪的爆炸扩散区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is like the widely scattered blast of a cosmic shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.30,0:27:25.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种高速粒子辐射射流打击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem with this jet of high-speed particles and radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.81,0:27:29.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2万光年外的效星系所带来的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hitting the little galaxy 20,000 light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.39,0:27:32.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是射流宽到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that the jet is wide enough
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.35,0:27:35.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖该星系里大量的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to encompass a large number of stars in this galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.36,0:27:41.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以该星系里的围绕任何恒星的任何行星上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So any creatures living on any planets
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.53,0:27:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何生物现在都险境重重了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting any stars in that galaxy are in serious trouble right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.66,0:27:50.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是我们的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What if it were our own Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.91,0:27:53.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在正遭死星系打击 又当如何呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}being blasted by the Death Star Galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.34,0:27:57.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把地球置于射流的路径上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Put Earth in the path of the jet,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.84,0:28:03.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对臭氧层的影响将会是严重和致命的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the effect on the ozone layer would be enormous and deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.80,0:28:07.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3C321发出的射流里的伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gamma rays from the jet in 3C321
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.51,0:28:10.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把氮转换成氮氧化物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}convert nitrogen gas into nitrous oxides.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.31,0:28:11.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是那些氮氧化物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's those nitrous oxides 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.83,0:28:13.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充当了破坏臭氧的催化剂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that actually act as a catalyst in the destruction of ozone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.02,0:28:18.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过数周 数月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So within a matter of weeks to months,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.19,0:28:20.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乃至一年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe up to a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.49,0:28:22.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,臭氧层就会被完全毁掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ozone layer will be completely obliterated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.11,0:28:25.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是个危险的后果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a nasty consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.70,0:28:30.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是和宇宙间所看到的许多现象一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But like many phenomena observed in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.87,0:28:37.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在着一个循环的悖论 - 有死才有生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is a recurring paradox-- from death comes life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.46,0:28:43.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3C321不仅在破坏 而且还在创造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}3C321 not only destroys, it also creates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:45.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我对3C321最感兴趣的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one of my favorite things about 3C321
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.55,0:28:47.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它清楚地证明了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is it demonstrates really clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.22,0:28:50.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞不只是吞噬着宇宙间的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that black holes don't just gobble everything up in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.18,0:28:52.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不全是毁灭的使者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're not all complete harbingers of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.64,0:28:55.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从3C321射出的射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The jet that is coming out in 3C321
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.56,0:28:57.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,击打着伙伴星系的这一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is hammering into the side of the companion galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.56,0:28:59.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然啦 那是破坏的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, yes, of course, that's a destructive force,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.48,0:29:01.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最终的遗产\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the ultimate legacy 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.16,0:29:04.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实是在互动中被压缩的气体云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually is that the gas clouds that get compressed during this interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.57,0:29:07.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上可以形成恒星 恒星又可以形成行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can actually form stars, and the stars can form planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.57,0:29:09.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而行星就有可能形成生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the planets may even form life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.37,0:29:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这种生死不息的美丽循环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's this beautiful cycle of birth and rebirth and destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.95,0:29:15.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是宇宙和黑洞的代名词\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's synonymous with the universe and black holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.13,0:29:18.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来有朝一日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One day in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.75,0:29:21.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们所处的银河系也可能与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our own Milky Way could form its own merger
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.92,0:29:27.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,邻近的仙女座星系合并成自己的联合体产生新的死星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the nearby Andromeda Galaxy and create a new Death Star Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.64,0:29:31.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其暴行一定会给地球带来厄运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a violent act that would certainly spell doom for the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.43,0:29:37.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样的事件很可能发生在未来的几十亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such an event would likely occur many billions of years in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.32,0:29:42.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过还有其它星际威胁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are other stellar threats
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.11,0:29:44.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正以高速闯入我们的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}streaking through our galaxy at high speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.32,0:29:50.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是超高速恒星 来势汹汹 势不可挡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are hypervelocity stars, and nothing can stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.87,0:29:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在人类眼里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To the human eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.29,0:30:00.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,群星在苍穹描绘出一幅宁静的画面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stars paint a tranquil picture in the heavens above.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.13,0:30:02.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是凑近一看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But take an up-close look.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.09,0:30:07.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中有些是濒临毁灭的死星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A select few are death stars on the verge of extinction,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.63,0:30:11.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些宇宙巨兽唯恐天下不乱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and these cosmic beasts are anything but peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.89,0:30:15.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星最终会烧尽其核心所有的氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually a star will burn through all the hydrogen in its core
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.60,0:30:16.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全部转变成氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and convert it all to helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.02,0:30:19.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦到那地步 它就必须质量大到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once it does that, it has to be massive enough
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.85,0:30:21.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够点燃氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be able to ignite the helium
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.73,0:30:23.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并将氦转换成重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and convert helium into heavier elements
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.61,0:30:25.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如碳 氧 氮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like carbon, oxygen and nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.61,0:30:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这会释放出巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this releases an enormous amount of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.82,0:30:33.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个过程也就是氢弹内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This process is the same release of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.12,0:30:35.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所发生的能量释放\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that goes on inside a hydrogen bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.13,0:30:43.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管它们极其暴戾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though they are incredibly violent,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.34,0:30:46.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是其中多数星会有朝一日耗尽燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of these stars will one day burn up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.17,0:30:48.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,悄无声息进入后半生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and slip quietly into the afterlife
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.51,0:30:52.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为星际僵尸 即所谓的白矮星 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as stellar corpses called white dwarf stars--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.55,0:30:55.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电子和原子构成的小球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}smallish balls of electrons and nuclei,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:30:58.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,注定不再会熊熊燃烧了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}destined to never again burn brightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.02,0:31:01.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有些是超大质量恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But some are supermassive stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.98,0:31:06.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,精力充沛的它们会终结于惊天动地的超新星爆发中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so energetic they end in a fantastic supernova explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.44,0:31:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时甚至会产生最大的爆炸 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sometimes even produce the largest of all blasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.87,0:31:13.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.70,0:31:22.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过对于一些大质量死星来说 终结意味着新的开端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for a few massive death stars, the end is a new beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.63,0:31:25.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来看看中子星的第二次生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Consider the second life of a neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.13,0:31:32.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大质量恒星爆发成为超新星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a massive star explodes in a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.47,0:31:36.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其星核有时会塌缩成一个黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its core sometimes collapses to form a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.56,0:31:39.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是更多的情形是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But much more frequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.52,0:31:43.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果其核心的质量不够 不能形成黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if the core isn't massive enough to create the black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.56,0:31:46.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所形成的东西几乎一样怪异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it forms something almost as weird,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.40,0:31:50.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星 个头不大但密度难以置信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a neutron star, a small but incredibly dense body.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.82,0:31:55.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它实际上具有大量的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It actually has a huge amount of material
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.49,0:31:57.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被压缩进了一个极小的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compressed into a very small space.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.58,0:32:00.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打个比方 你将我们整个太阳的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you have, for example, the mass of our entire Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.79,0:32:05.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挤进只有几十英里的空间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}squeezed into a space maybe only a couple tens of miles across.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.09,0:32:08.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重力极强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.80,0:32:12.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以至于恒星的原子里的质子和电子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the protons and electrons inside the atoms of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.05,0:32:15.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上被挤在一起形成了中子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are actually pushed together to form neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.68,0:32:19.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星可以稳定存续数十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a neutron star can remain stable for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:22.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutron stars by themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.60,0:32:25.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会对宇宙邻居构成威胁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pose no danger to their celestial neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.61,0:32:28.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除非它们能找到搭档\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unless they can find a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.57,0:32:32.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还能看到恒星的死亡场景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can also get another death scenario for stars
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.40,0:32:37.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗中子星之间好像有共同自杀的协定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where there's a sort of mutual suicide pact between two neutron stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.29,0:32:42.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们叫做共轨中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are called co-orbiting neutron stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.71,0:32:45.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其现象开始时 两颗中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a phenomenon initiated when two neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.54,0:32:48.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了一种亲密但注定一死的关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}begin an intimate, but doomed relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.09,0:32:52.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的轨道在数十亿年后会收窄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their orbit narrows over millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.92,0:32:56.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直至它们最终相碰 化为一道闪光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until they finally meet in a flash of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.64,0:33:02.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此过程中 它们会产生一个剧烈的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in so doing, they can generate a violent explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.81,0:33:04.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某种意义上的第二次生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a second life in a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.69,0:33:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以存在有两种不同的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's two different types of gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.56,0:33:09.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有短时间爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's short bursts,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.02,0:33:12.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其持续时间不足2秒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which have durations of less than two seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.82,0:33:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为短时间爆发产生于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we think that short bursts are produced
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.07,0:33:17.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星的合并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by merging neutron stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.49,0:33:22.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短时间爆发不同于大质量恒星塌缩所产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The short bursts are different than the longer GRBs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.66,0:33:25.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间较长的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}produced by collapsing massive stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.46,0:33:31.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗碰撞的中子星所发出的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gamma ray burst emitted by two colliding neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.34,0:33:35.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然时间短 但很强烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be short, but it's powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.93,0:33:38.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等于太阳毕生发出的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}equal to the energy released by the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.22,0:33:42.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2秒不到的时间里释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over its entire lifetime in less than two seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.48,0:33:45.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的担忧何在？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The worry for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.85,0:33:48.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少有两打成双共轨的中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At least two dozen pairs of orbiting neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.90,0:33:51.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在于银河系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exist in the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.48,0:33:55.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很近的伽玛射线暴 首要的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A very nearby gamma ray burst, first and foremost,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.90,0:33:58.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会剥去大部分臭氧层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would get rid of much of the ozone layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.53,0:34:01.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那会给地球造成灾难性的后果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That could have disastrous effects on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.12,0:34:10.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有估计认为 暴虐的中子星合并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some estimates hold that a violent neutron star merger
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.63,0:34:16.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一亿年会有一次发生在距太阳3000光年的范围内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}occurs within about 3,000 light-years of the Sun every 100 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.84,0:34:20.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这大概相当于地球化石记录所记载的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about the same interval as the mass extinction events
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:23.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大规模灭绝事件的间隔时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}recorded in the Earth's fossil record.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.22,0:34:26.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是巧合 还是我们应该担心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is it coincidence, or should we worry
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.77,0:34:29.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗垂死的恒星最后的探戈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the last tango of two dying stars
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.31,0:34:31.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能最终因为致命的伽玛射线轰击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might eventually blast the Earth's ozone layer
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.94,0:34:35.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的臭氧层 进而改变地球呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with deadly gamma rays and alter the planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.07,0:34:38.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家无从回答\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists don't know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.41,0:34:44.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风险或许就如同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The chances are probably about the same
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.66,0:34:48.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗速逃星冒失地闯入地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a runaway star plowing headlong into the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.75,0:34:51.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能性极小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a remote possibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.96,0:34:54.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不能掉以轻心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but fearsome to contemplate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.30,0:35:00.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你实际上有可能看到群星簇拥\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can actually have the possibility that a collection of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.76,0:35:03.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许都积聚在同一个街区里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that perhaps were all together in the same neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.39,0:35:04.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,彼此互动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}interacting with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.93,0:35:09.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时会弹射出一颗恒星 离家游荡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes ejects a star, just to wander off on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.77,0:35:13.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据我们所知\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As far as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.27,0:35:16.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尚无游星奔我们而来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are no wandering stars headed our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.11,0:35:19.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是发生那样的事情 将会是相当有趣的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if that were to happen, it could be quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.62,0:35:25.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到的场景是围绕太阳的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One scenario could see the Earth's orbit around the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.45,0:35:29.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会受到游星引力的骚扰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}disrupted by the gravitational pull of the wandering star.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.12,0:35:35.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个戏剧性的后果就是这样一颗游星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One dramatic possibility is that such a wandering star
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.09,0:35:38.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会将地球踹出整个太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}simply kicks the Earth entirely out of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.17,0:35:41.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得我们到处流浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so we're now wandering around
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.26,0:35:43.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,失去了能量的来源 - 太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without a source of energy, the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.97,0:35:47.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无人知道结局如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one really knows what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.06,0:35:48.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这取决于接近的角度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It really depends upon the angle of approach,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.68,0:35:50.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该星的质量 等等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mass of the star, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.69,0:35:56.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,游星的速度可达到每秒60英里 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wandering stars can travel at up to 60 miles per second--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.69,0:35:58.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快 但还是未达到快得足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fast, but still not fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.48,0:36:01.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,摆脱银河系的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to escape the Milky Way's gravitational pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.49,0:36:08.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是有一些涡轮增压型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are some supercharged turbo models
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.62,0:36:13.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上可以挣脱逃逸 飞进宇宙间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that could actually break free and rocket out into the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.75,0:36:17.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们叫做超高速星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are called hypervelocity stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.30,0:36:21.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高速星是太阳一类的普通恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hypervelocity stars are normal stars like the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.67,0:36:23.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了它们跑出星系的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except that they're moving out of the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.80,0:36:25.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大大超过时速百万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at well over a million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.51,0:36:28.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那已经超越了银河系的逃逸速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's beyond the escape velocity of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.14,0:36:35.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要有速度才能让一对普通的共轨恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The need for speed begins with a normal pair of co-orbiting stars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.35,0:36:39.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十分靠近黑洞的边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that get too close to the edge of a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.69,0:36:43.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像发生故障的阿波罗13号指令舱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as the disabled Apollo 13 command module
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.74,0:36:47.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过机动接近月球的轨道来提升速度一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}got a boost to velocity by maneuvering close to the Moon's orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.70,0:36:53.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高速星从黑洞获得巨大的引力反冲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the hypervelocity star gets a huge gravitational kick from the black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.96,0:36:56.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,割断与其双胞胎伙伴的关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}severing the bond with its binary partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.50,0:36:59.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最靠近黑洞的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The star closest to the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.71,0:37:01.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会陷入围绕黑洞的贴身轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is captured into a very tight orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.38,0:37:03.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样它就无能为力了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}around the black hole, and so it loses this energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.01,0:37:05.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一颗恒星就获得了能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The other star gains that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.43,0:37:08.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果就以这种极大的速度被弹射出来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is ejected with this very large velocity as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.52,0:37:16.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高速星的射出很像是弹弓效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ejection of a hypervelocity star is much like a slingshot effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.06,0:37:20.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞬间双星的轨道被打破\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the instant the binary star's orbit is broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.36,0:37:25.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高速星以极大的力道被射入浩瀚的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the hypervelocity star is launched with incredibIe force into the void of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.24,0:37:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一经被逐出银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've been voted out of the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.24,0:37:33.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就注定漂泊在无边无际的太空之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're destined to drift into the empty depths of intergalactic space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.62,0:37:38.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些恒星影响到地球是非常不可能的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's very unlikely that these stars will ever affect the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.71,0:37:43.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是 这些超高速星的老死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately, the eventual death of these speedy stars
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.13,0:37:45.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会发生在离太阳很远很远的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will occur far away from our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.68,0:37:52.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些在我们街区里的死星才是我们需要警惕的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the death stars on our own block we need to keep an eye on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.77,0:37:56.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙时间里 它们的引信已经点绕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In cosmic time, their fuses are lit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.89,0:38:01.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们首当其冲它们的湮灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we have a front-row seat to their annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.12,0:38:12.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙偏远的角落里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In remote corners of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.37,0:38:15.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无数恒星正在死囚牢房里等待着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}countless stars are biding their time on death row,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.91,0:38:18.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被处以壮丽暴虐的极刑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sentenced to spectacular, violent endings.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.96,0:38:25.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离家不远处 有几十颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Closer to home, there are a few dozen stars
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:28.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在距地球20光年的范围内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}within 20 light-years of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.13,0:38:31.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中有些正在准备后事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a few of these are preparing for death.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.47,0:38:37.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为我们对普通超新星的威胁是安全的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think we're safe from the dangers of a normal supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.77,0:38:41.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于伽玛射线暴的情况 我们不敢打包票\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the case of a gamma ray burst, we're not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.15,0:38:46.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中有在船底座伊塔星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One is in the stellar system Eta Carinae,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.03,0:38:50.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗超新星比我们太阳大100倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a supermassive star about 100 times bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.49,0:38:53.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亮100万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a million times more luminous than the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.66,0:38:57.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1843年 积聚的压力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1843, a buildup of pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.83,0:39:01.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,点燃的巨大的光喷发 在地球上都能看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ignited a gigantic eruption of light seen from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.67,0:39:04.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是该星存活了下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the star survived
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.17,0:39:07.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了尘埃云 叫做星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and formed a dust cloud called a nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.01,0:39:10.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在8000光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At a distance of just 8,000 light-years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.84,0:39:14.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们首当其冲它的毁灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'll have a front-row seat to its annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.47,0:39:17.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为它会变成黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think it's going to turn into a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.52,0:39:20.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在现在到未来的100万年里的某个时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometime between now and the next million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.48,0:39:23.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着它的塌缩 它有足够的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as it collapses, it has enough matter
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.52,0:39:27.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以产生强烈的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it can produce a powerful gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.45,0:39:32.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不像沃尔夫-拉叶星104\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike the star Wolf-Rayet 104,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.37,0:39:35.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,船底座伊塔星并没有把我们纳入它的准星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eta Carinae doesn't have us in its crosshairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.04,0:39:38.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道船底座伊塔的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that the rotation of Eta Carinae
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.54,0:39:40.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并没有正对地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not pointed towards Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.04,0:39:44.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们很幸运 伽玛射线柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So lucky for us, the pulse of the gamma ray
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.79,0:39:48.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不会直接影响到地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not going to be directly impacting Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.93,0:39:52.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.22,0:39:59.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发有可能会是人类所见证到的最亮的超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the explosion will likely be the brightest supernova ever witnessed by mankind 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.27,0:40:04.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除非冠军旁落另一颗死星竞争者 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unless the title goes to another death star contender
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.86,0:40:07.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是更加靠近地球的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's even closer to Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.23,0:40:09.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参宿四\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.40,0:40:13.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,位于500光年外的猎户座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Located in the Orion constellation about 500 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.74,0:40:18.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参宿四正快速耗尽其最后的核燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse is quickly burning through the last of its nuclear fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.25,0:40:24.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参宿四是颗很大的恒星 其质量是太阳的20倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse is a very massive star, about 20 times the mass of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.71,0:40:27.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会在50万年里爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's within half a million years of exploding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.92,0:40:30.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们关注到参宿四\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People have been noticing that Betelgeuse
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.21,0:40:33.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的数十年里变化很大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been changing a lot over the last decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.43,0:40:37.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它实际上大幅收缩 约有15%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's actually shrunk considerably, about 15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.85,0:40:39.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意味着什么 无人知晓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What that means, no one is sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.89,0:40:41.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是大家都不敢掉以轻心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but everyone's keeping an eye on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.56,0:40:47.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些科学家认为参宿四可能会释放出伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some scientists believe Betelgeuse could unleash a gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.86,0:40:51.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球人对此无庸担忧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People on Earth have little to fear if it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.28,0:40:56.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和船底座伊塔星一样 其星轴指向安全地远离地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like Eta Carinae, the star's axis points safely away from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.45,0:41:00.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅如此 而且参宿四还可能具有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only that, but Betelgeuse may also have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.54,0:41:02.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内置的爆炸屏障\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a built-in blast shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.12,0:41:06.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其爆发会相对平常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its explosion will be relatively normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.75,0:41:08.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不会是伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't be a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.92,0:41:11.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为参宿四存在着厚厚的氢气外壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because there's this thick hydrogen envelope in Betelgeuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.96,0:41:13.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢气外壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that hydrogen envelope
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.34,0:41:18.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会阻挡住喷射中的粒子辐射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will probably prevent the jet of particles and radiation from emerging.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.97,0:41:24.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辐射流里会有大量的物质送出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's too much material through which the jet of radiation would have to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.64,0:41:29.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参宿四会短时间内强烈发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Betelgeuse will shine intensely for a brief moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.77,0:41:35.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是比不上我们最近的恒星 - 太阳的最后时刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it won't compare to the final moments of our nearest star, the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.99,0:41:40.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳这样的普通恒星 健康长寿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Average stars like our Sun have nice, long life spans,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.95,0:41:42.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们幸运的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fortunately for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:45.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳才度过了它百亿年寿命的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our Sun is about halfway through its 10-billion-year lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.46,0:41:47.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它才45亿岁左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's about 4 1/2 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.67,0:41:49.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,步入中年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That makes it middle-aged.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.38,0:41:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家估计太阳还能活50亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists estimate that the Sun will live another 5 billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.67,0:41:59.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们的问题会更早产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but our problems could begin much sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.72,0:42:03.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳在逐步变得明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our own Sun is very gradually getting brighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.02,0:42:05.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变得更加强劲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}getting more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.94,0:42:10.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在50亿年 肯定是100亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And within a half a billion, certainly a billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.69,0:42:12.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球将会变得非常的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth will become so hot
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.11,0:42:14.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋将会蒸发殆尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the oceans will have evaporated away.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.94,0:42:18.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此我们是不会有四五十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we don't quite have 4 or 5 billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.20,0:42:20.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来操心这个问题了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to worry about this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.53,0:42:25.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须要对此操心的时间尺度就几亿年的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have to worry about it on time scales of hundreds of millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.50,0:42:30.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳让地球聊无生机的几十亿年后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Billions of years after the Sun renders the Earth devoid of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.63,0:42:34.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会进入最后阶段 所谓的红巨星时代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will enter a final phase, known as a red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.80,0:42:38.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不可能爆发成为超新星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can't explode and produce a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.22,0:42:40.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它个头不够\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's not massive enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.56,0:42:46.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是大多数科学家都赞同最后的篇章\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But most scientists agree on the final chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.68,0:42:50.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为红巨星 其密度会减小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a red giant, its density will decrease,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.52,0:42:56.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会向外膨胀 吞噬它的近邻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Sun will balloon outward, devouring its nearest neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.28,0:42:59.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此阶段 红巨星阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this stage, the red giant stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.91,0:43:02.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会膨胀 吞噬水星 金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun will probably expand and engulf Mercury, Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.87,0:43:05.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许还有地球本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and maybe even Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.04,0:43:09.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 那几乎是地球的末日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that would pretty much be the end of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.38,0:43:17.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙间所有的死星威胁中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all the dangerous death stars in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.13,0:43:22.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最有可能摧毁地球的就是我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one most likely to destroy the Earth is our own Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.76,0:43:28.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然这标志着我们星球的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While it marks our planet's ultimate end,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.23,0:43:31.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它只不过是宇宙循环的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's merely a part of the cycle of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.69,0:43:37.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死星杀生 但是它们也是生命的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Death stars take life, but they are also the origin of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.15,0:43:40.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们体内的重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The heavy elements in our bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.90,0:43:45.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毫不夸张地说是产生于前几代的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}quite literally were generated by previous generations of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.95,0:43:50.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是自星际爆发中射入宇宙的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ejected into the cosmos by stellar explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.62,0:43:56.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此如果不是发生了某些恒星在其生命结束时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we would not be here if it were not for the fact that some stars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.13,0:43:59.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剧烈的爆发的话 我们就不会在这里了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explode violently at the end of their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.76,0:44:01.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正如卡尔 萨根说过的那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As Carl Sagan used to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.38,0:44:05.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是星际物质组成的 我们是星尘组成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"We are made of star stuff, we are made of stardust."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.14,0:44:10.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着爆发的不断进行 产生出重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the explosions continue, the resulting heavy elements
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.64,0:44:14.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许有朝一日再次播下生命的基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may one day re-seed the very foundations of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.98,0:44:16.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远离银河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far from the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.23,0:44:23.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙新的一角的一颗新的蓝色星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a new blue planet
